{"comments":"BitStream — Bit-level operations for QR code encoding.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nQR codes are encoded at the bit level. This module provides:\n- A pure functional BitStream type\n- Bit manipulation operations\n- Conversion to/from bytes (codewords)\n\nAll operations are pure — no mutation, no FFI.\n\n## QR Encoding Process\n\n1. Data → Segments (mode + data bits)\n2. Segments → BitStream\n3. BitStream + padding → Codewords\n4. Codewords + Reed-Solomon → Final data\n\n## Bit Ordering\n\nQR codes use MSB-first (most significant bit first) ordering.\nWhen we write 4 bits of value 5 (binary 0101), we write:\nposition 0: 0, position 1: 1, position 2: 0, position 3: 1\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude (basic operations)\n- Data.Array (bit storage)\n- Data.EuclideanRing (div, mod for bit math)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Element","Compound","QRCode","Encoding","BitStream"],"BitStream"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[161,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Element/Compound/QRCode/Encoding/BitStream.purs","start":[161,1]},"title":"eqBitStream"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Element","Compound","QRCode","Encoding","BitStream"],"BitStream"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[164,81],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Element/Compound/QRCode/Encoding/BitStream.purs","start":[163,1]},"title":"showBitStream"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Semigroup"],"Semigroup"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{